Aston Villa beat Liverpool 2-1 in the FA Cup final at Wembley on Saturday . 
  Randy Lerner missed the game because of a family bereavement . 
  The American owner is expected to attend the final against Arsenal on May 30 . 
  Villa chief executive Tom Fox said Lerner was ' ecstatic' with the win . 
  Villa can qualify for the Europa League by beating Arsenal . 
 